SUMMARY:Azure Decoded: Ground AI Apps with Fabric IQ’s Semantic Foundati
 on
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nIn this episode of Azure Decoded\, 
 our team breaks down what Fabric IQ unlocks: a shared semantic foundation 
 that helps teams and AI reason over data. You’ll see a practical demo of
  how Fabric IQ unifies business semantics across data\, models\, and rules
 \; then powers data agents that ground natural-language questions in consi
 stent definitions of entities\, relationships\, and metrics for more trust
 worthy answers. We’ll also cover how these agents can be used inside and
  outside Fabric (including via Microsoft Foundry)\, so data engineers\, de
 velopers\, and AI devs can move faster from insight to action with less pr
 ompt wrangling.\n\n**What you’ll learn:**\n• How Fabric IQ creates a s
 hared semantic foundation that unifies business entities\, relationships\,
  and metrics across data\, models\, and systems\n• How to build and use 
 Fabric IQ–powered data agents that ground natural‑language questions i
 n business context and return more accurate\, trustworthy insights across 
 tabular\, graph\, and real‑time data.\n• How to apply Fabric IQ in rea
 l-world developer workflows\, including a live demo showing how data engin
 eers and AI developers can move faster from data to decisions using Fabric
 \, Foundry\, and agent-ready architectures.\n\n**Who should attend:** Deve
 lopers\, AI Developers\, Data Engineers\, solution architects\, and techni
 cal professionals\n\n***\n\n[Understand Microsoft Fabric IQ fundamentals](
 https://learn.microsoft.com/training/modules/understand-fabric-iq-fundamen
 tals/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26878_webpage_reactor)\n\n📌 This session is a par
 t of a series! Learn more **[here](https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor
 /series/S-1644/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1644_webpage_reactor)**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3136
 70528/
